    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="120"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">548.G1/75a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Hamilton</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-20T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 20, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83. Your 119, April 19, 6 p.m. Last paragraph of yours under reference:
                    Department accepts your statement as a correct expression of its views and
                    hereby confirms your statement. Department will take note of your telegram for
                    future consideration. There is no doubt of the fact that the British Government
                    agreed to the use of the Executive Committee of the Intergovernmental Committee
                    and <pb facs="0165" n="155" xml:id="pg_155"/> subsequently of the organization
                    of the Intergovernmental Committee itself for the purposes under discussion and
                    that at the time of Mr. Eden’s visit to Washington<note n="28" xml:id="d120fn28"
                        >March 12–30, 1943; see <ref target="frus1943v03#pg_1">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, pp. 1</ref> ff.</note> this was expressly
                    confirmed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
